ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Compared with how you used to feel, during the past few weeks, have you frequently felt: Pleased about having accomplished something?
Compared with how you used to feel, during the past few weeks, have you frequently felt: Proud because someone complimented you on something?
Compared with how you used to feel, during the past few weeks, have you frequently felt: That things were going your way?
Compared with how you used to feel, during the past few weeks, have you frequently felt: Particularly excited or interested in something?
Compared with how you used to feel, during the past few weeks, have you frequently felt: On top of the world?
Compared with how you used to feel, during the past few weeks, have you frequently felt: So restless that you couldn't sit long in a chair?
Compared with how you used to feel, during the past few weeks, have you frequently felt: Very lonely or remote from other people?
Compared with how you used to feel, during the past few weeks, have you frequently felt: Bored?
Compared with how you used to feel, during the past few weeks, have you frequently felt: Depressed or very unhappy?
Compared with how you used to feel, during the past few weeks, have you frequently felt: Upset because someone criticized you?

Notes: Difference of negative affect score from positive affect score
